Male . Tergite 10 and sternite 9 of male genital segment as in
Figs. 160, 161
. Aedeagus relatively small, 1.9–2.6 mm long, median lobe generally wide, sub-triangular (
Fig. 162
), rarely markedly narrower and variably shaped, but always apically pointed (
Figs. 163, 164
); parameres symmetrical (
Figs. 162, 165
); inner sac ribbon-like, wide and long, folded on itself, covered with little scales.

Distribution. Distributed in West, Central and East Africa (
Fig. 147
).
